cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of driver distraction identification using deep learning-based solutions. The proposed method involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and genetic algorithms for classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of ensembles and genetic algorithms, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the effect of different visual elements in distraction detection, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning-based solutions, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of a dataset and the evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
